    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I hear you, but some commentators argue that even if individual values are strong, the sheer scale of the demographic change creates a \"tipping point\" where the existing social cohesion just breaks down. They talk about how rapid shifts in language and community norms can fundamentally alter the political landscape in ways that make old institutions less functional. Don't you think there's some merit to the idea that social stability relies on a certain level of cultural continuity?",
